            <div type="translation" resp="part:emfr">
                
                <p n="1-3">
                    So that there be a <foreign>cōtaṇa-kāṇi</foreign>
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">there is</supplied> a land that has been given.
                </p>
                
                <p n="4-9">
                    So that there be a <foreign>cōtaṇa-kāṇi</foreign>,
                    we have given as long as the moon and the sun
                    seven <foreign>mā</foreign>s
                    ...
                    we, the temple officers.
                </p>
            </div>
            
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>This short inscription contains no date at its beginning. It is inscribed on the bottom part of the pilaster left of zone D of inscription <ref target="DHARMA_INSTiruvavatuturai10009.xml">Tiruvāvaṭutuṟai 10009</ref> (ARIE/1924-1925/B/1925/104) and appears, by its location, to be connected to this inscription <ref target="DHARMA_INSTiruvavatuturai10009.xml">Tiruvāvaṭutuṟai 10009</ref>.</p>
            </div>
            
